cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SI 

This paper deals with the use of machine learning techniques to detect cyber attacks, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper specifically focuses on the use of a neural network classifier (cs.LG) and a GAN model (cs.AI) to generate more attack samples for a dataset that is initially unbalanced. The use of neural networks and generative models also falls under the categories of neural networks (cs.NE) and social and information networks (cs.SI).
